Parks Name Meaning in English

What does the name Parks mean? What is the meaning of the name Parks, lucky number, lucky stone, origin and religion.

Park Name Meaning. English and Scottish: from Middle English, Old French parc 'park'; a metonymic occupational name for someone employed in a park or a topographic name for someone who lived in or near a park.

Parks Name Meaning, Origin & Details

Meaning: A park-keeper, a gamekeeper Short Info: Parker was the butler to Lady Penelope in 1960s TV puppet series "Thunderbirds". Details: Originally a surname, meaning "keeper of the park".
